# Claude Code Caracal SDK Playbook

This folder is a copy-paste Claude Code setup for integrating Caracal SDKs into real applications, services, agents, and platforms.

## Use it for

- understanding the user's product, architecture, frameworks, agent runtimes, and deployment modes before integrating
- scoping complete versus feature-specific Caracal integrations
- verifying the SDK surface against Caracal, SDK, and framework/provider documentation
- selecting stable or release-candidate SDK versions for the detected runtime
- implementing thin, production-grade integrations that reuse existing patterns
- validating integrations with the codebase's existing tests and checks

## Install

Copy `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/` into the repository where users want Claude Code to help integrate Caracal.

## Behavior

Claude should:

- understand the codebase and confirm scope before writing code
- verify SDK, framework, and provider behavior from documentation before assumptions
- prefer stable or release-candidate SDK versions, never alpha unless asked
- generate complete integrations, never mock or placeholder wiring unless requested
- invoke deeper agent analysis only when explicitly needed
- store secrets in environment variables or the user's secret manager
- suggest thin workaround layers when direct support is limited

## Not for

- Rego policy authoring
- provider dashboard field mapping
- hardcoding secrets or inventing undocumented SDK APIs

If an integration case is unsupported or needs larger product changes, direct the user to [the Caracal issue form](https://github.com/Garudex-Labs/caracal/issues/new/choose) and, when deeper support is needed, `contact@caracal.run`.
